  "response": "Learning Chinese in 2 years by studying 1 hour per day is possible, but your progress will depend on several factors:\n\nRealistic Expectations:\n- You'll likely reach a basic conversational level\n- Proficiency will depend on your learning method and dedication\n- Reading and writing will be more challenging than speaking/listening\n\nRecommended Learning Strategies:\n1. Use language learning apps (Duolingo, HelloChinese)\n2. Take online courses\n3. Practice with language exchange websites\n4. Watch Chinese movies/TV shows with subtitles\n5. Listen to Chinese podcasts\n6. Use textbooks and grammar guides\n7. Practice speaking with native speakers online\n\nDifficulty Levels:\n- Speaking: Moderate difficulty\n- Listening: Moderate difficulty\n- Reading: More challenging\n- Writing: Most difficult\n\nEstimated Proficiency after 2 years:\n- HSK 2-3 level (basic conversational skills)\n- Can handle simple daily conversations\n- Basic reading and writing abilities\n\nTips for Success:\n- Be consistent\n- Use varied learning resources\n- Practice pronunciation\n- Immerse yourself in the language\n- Consider occasional tutoring or language classes\n\nRemember, individual learning speed varies, so your progress might differ from these estimates.",
